		<div id="post_message_1178047">
                  
                  It would have been better if they never offered to not merge Florendyl than to have put up a poll, then go back on what they promised. I don't know who they are talking to, but the vast majority of people on FLo are seriously ticked off about this. It's the usual story - you have a very vocal minority crying very loudly about needing a merge; but they are still a minority.<br />
<br />
Server population <i>has</i> dropped. But not because of lack of grouping - the number one reason is because of the constant crashing which they only partially fixed last patch. If they pushed out bug fixes and stability fixes faster, they would have preserved the population better. Prople have just gotten the idea (right or wrong) that SOE doesn't really care about the game or the players, and just want to lure them over to EQ2 with the Station Pass plan.<br />
<br />
People <i>are</i> concerned with the population, but I don't think telling us it was our choice, then going back on that, was the right call. They said from the start, if the population was too low <i>after</i> the merge and didn't get any better, they would close Florendyl. So why didn't they do that, like they said? This is a major PR mistake, IMO.
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
